# 📍 Day 20 — Disaster Recovery

## 🎯 Objective

Understand Disaster Recovery (DR) strategies in AWS and how they balance cost, availability, and recovery speed.

---

## 💥 What is Disaster Recovery?

* Planning system recovery after failure/disaster
* Ensures business continuity

---

## 📌 DR Strategies

### 🟢 Backup & Restore

* Store backups in AWS
* Restore during disaster

### 📌 Benefits

* Lowest cost
* Simple approach

### 📌 Drawback

* Higher recovery time

---

## 🟡 Pilot Light

* Minimal critical infrastructure always running
* Scale up when disaster occurs

### 📌 Benefits

* Faster recovery than backup & restore
* Lower cost than full standby

---

## 🟠 Warm Standby

* Smaller version of production environment active
* Can quickly scale to full capacity

### 📌 Benefits

* Faster recovery
* Better availability

---

## 🔴 Multi-Site / Active-Active

* Full production environments in multiple regions
* Traffic distributed across regions

### 📌 Benefits

* Highest availability
* Lowest downtime

### 📌 Drawback

* Highest cost

---

## ⚖️ Key Concepts

| Strategy         | Cost    | Recovery Speed |
| ---------------- | ------- | -------------- |
| Backup & Restore | Low     | Slow           |
| Pilot Light      | Medium  | Faster         |
| Warm Standby     | Higher  | Fast           |
| Active-Active    | Highest | Fastest        |

---

## 💡 Key Learnings

* DR strategy depends on business requirements
* Lower downtime usually means higher cost
* RTO & RPO are critical decision factors

---

## 🚧 Challenges Faced

* Understanding differences between DR strategies
* Relating cost with recovery speed

